    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "scipy.stats.gaussian_kde seems to be the culprit here ...\npandas uses this to create the kde plots\n\n``` python\n\nIn [119]: from scipy.stats import gaussian_kde\n\nIn [120]: y = [10,26,36,64,69,73,76,79,80,81,81,82,83,86,89,93,98,126,136,152]\n\nIn [121]: gaussian_kde(y).evaluate([70, 80, 90])\nOut[121]: array([0, 0, 0])\n\nIn [122]: y = [10.0,26,36,64,69,73,76,79,80,81,81,82,83,86,89,93,98,126,136,152]\n\nIn [123]: gaussian_kde(y).evaluate([70, 80, 90])\nOut[123]: array([ 0.01214366,  0.01385886,  0.01268444])\n```\n"
